rComments: Amazing prof. Great lectures, provides helpful real-world examples and is very willing and able to provide additional help outside of class. Different from the typical prof you find in these types of courses.

Very good professor, teaches you how to apply the material in real life examples. In b57 class he taught us how regression can be applied to machine learning concepts. For the final exam, he told us exactly what was expected.
kinda theoretic lectures on graph theory but enjoys giving students real world examples using cards and how to hack networks

There's no point in going to his lectures. All he does is write down theorems and he doesn't go over any examples. He's very disorganized, too. However, his exams are incredibly easy and straightforward, so it's still possible to do well in his course without attending lectures.

Let us know for the get go we would have to put in the work. Likes to go on tangents (pardon the pun) about history and anecdotes, but also is particular to let people know its wont be part of the final. Overall enjoyed the class,par

he has 3 weeks that don't teach us and let TA teach us, the midterm only 5 questions, each question worth 20 points.... but he is a very smart teacher, he is only around 24 years old. I hope he can change his teaching style.

Heavy focus on explaining the big picture  and "inspiring" students. Even though he takes quite some time to go over some abstract material, he clearly  stated that we were not expected to know the proofs for the midterm. This was the case and as a result, midterm was very fair and exactly what we expected. Would take again

Mostly focused on general concepts and TONS of definitions. Not enough examples given. He rarely ever posted anything. No solutions given to assignments and no notes posted or ANYTHING. Exam boundaries were not clear. No sync b/w prof and TAs. You just feel on your own in this course. AVOID if you can.
solid lectures, a bit complicated and confusing at times, but knows what he's talking about
I don't always understand exactly where he's getting at, but have found that going to office hours, he is quite happy to help and explain things as many times as necessary !
Very knowledgeable prof. Definitely knows what hes doing but since he doesn't do examples with class instead just posted on notes, kinda hard to follow

I go to all his morning classes hoping would "teach" us something useful, like give proper examples on how to apply and uses these techniques and methods. He literally has nothing to teach and stalls majority of the time. Say a word, slips his coffee, flicks his hair and repeats. Don't even know if he knows that how to solve problems himself.. _
early lectures, insightful at some times

Reads off lecture likes that has tons of errors... everything he does annoys me. Can't teach at all. Tried to teach something with a simple term but failed. Cannot do math on the spot so he heavily relies on his own notes that's pretty useless anyways... how did he even get this position????

I never went to his class once, it's too early. I followed his lecture notes, web assign, and the book. Watched some Khan Academy, and Patrickjmt to understand what was going on.  Made the midterm really hard but bell curved our marks. Final was a bit easier but still hard. Got a 4.0 in this course, despite doing bad in MATA30. My TA was helpful.

he was not a prof i would look up to since his lecture notes were posted 5 minutes before 8am class because he had no time to make one ahead. oh, and a lot of 'words' on the note. also, class average turnt to be a d plus. he talks to himself, lectures end early (once 2 hr lecture were cut in 45mins) but exams are not 'fair.'
Nice guy to talk to. Very knowledgable. Just too fast on lectures.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Not an interactive teacher, and reads notes off paper. Homework questions assigned by t.a's, so hard to keep track of what is being taught.

Decent prof.  Pros:   Knows a lot about math Tells interesting stories Interesting examples   Cons:  Talks really fast so its hard to follow sometimes Reads off of a paper instead of using chalkboard like most math profs do Very hard midterm (but was bellcurved)
greatest professor for math, made math fun to learn and learnt that there is a million dollar math question, and volumes, series and such

Pay attention to the proofing part of lectures, even though as we all know, proofing is something usually the math students' concern, instead of science students'... The reason is simple, he will test you that in the exam!!!

midterm was fair but since everyone was use to Sophies easy midterms,werent expecting more conceptual/enriched thinking questions. If I knew this beforehand Id know how to study it better. In lect Id like to see you write out questions like you did with the lect on volume where you drew it out on the board, and more classparticipation/discussion.
He is really nice and giving out so many good feedback based on the course materials

Classes were at 8am  but Louis makes it bearable with his enthusiasm for this course. Louis knows his stuff for this course but the lecture notes don't have too much examples so the textbook would help. In office hours, he clarifies concepts so much better so it's advised to go. Watch out for the midterm and final. Dresses nice as well!

Even though my class was at 8am and you'd think its impossible to motivate yourself to come to school that early for calculus, Louis' passion for the material and his quirky mannerisms make the class much easier to attend. He is a very approachable guy and when I went to his office hours he always did his best to make sure my question was answered.

His lectures are fast and a lot may fly over your head initially, but paying attention will be beneficial even if you don't get all the proofs.  There aren't too many examples in class so reading the textbook after will really help.  He is a super interesting, super excited prof and his lectures are definitely worth attending, even at 8am.
does not apply the theories to examples and is very abstract as to what is expected from students. unrealistic tests.
He is a good prof, its too bad the lectures are at 8 in the morning. It does not really help :P. Really enjoy going to the lectures since he seems to always make them enjoyable.

Very good professor, knows his stuff well, and is willing to help outside of class. However, he sometimes treats all his students like they're on the same level as him, and doesn't explain things that should be explained because I assume he thinks it's something everyone should know already.

His mid-term was very hard, but he does hint to what the questions may be in his review list. He is good if you can pick up concepts quickly; terrible for those who learn with examples. Mixed emotions with this professor really. Good luck to all those taking this course with him.

The professor is very unclear when he is teaching because he goes very fast in class. He doesn't go thoroughly over the examples on that concept learned can be applied in many ways. He had no practice midterms or practice questions as to what to expect on the midterm. The midterm DESTROYED everyone whether you were the best math student or not.

Professor is pretty funny and helpful with questions online/ in class. He goes pretty fast in class. The midterm was a bloodbath...  He gave us a list of what he expected us to know from each lecture, a lot of it was not on the test. It would have been better if he assigned practice questions like the questions he may ask on the midterm.

Very funny and intelligible prof.  He seems to move very fast in his lectures, but you'll get adjusted really quickly to it and his teaching style.  His handwriting is somewhat small and hard to see on the chalkboard, so moving up to the front is a good idea if you want to take some good notes down. Style always on fleek, he gets a chili pepper.

He's an awesome professor. At first I thought he would be super fast with his lectures but I got adjusted to it. He gives one of the best lectures in the campus. He's very informative and helpful. If you do the homework you'll do well. In addition to that, he's pretty easy on the eyes ;)
Very insightful and entertaining lectures.

It can be a little hard to read his handwriting, and the projector clarity never really got fixed, but overall gives pretty clear lectures and is really easy-going. It did seem like too much time was spent on the simple review chapters in the beginning, but generally well-paced. Sometimes examples get sped through, so you can't always take notes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: funny lectures. Gets hard to fill in the handouts sincee he has them done already but most of the stuff is writtten on the board anyways. Overall great teacher

Guess i'll be a pioneer& rate him first. Great professor, extremely humorous lectures. Very approachable, knowledgable, and helpful. After a long day of monotone lectures, you'll adore him and his teaching style.  Also great at flipping his hair. Looks like he came from a Burberry photo shoot every class. Chilli peppers for personality.
